The present invention is illustrated by way of example, and not by way of limitation, in the figures of the accompanying drawings and in which like reference numerals refer to similar elements in which;


FIG. 1 is a block diagram depicting a computer system having a data storage device in the form of a secondary memory;


FIG. 2 is a block diagram depicting a conventional data storage device, as in FIG. 1;


FIG. 3 depicts a perspective view of an exemplary disk drive;


FIG. 4 depicts a top view of a printed circuit board of the disk drive of FIG. 3;


FIG. 5 depicts a top view of a disk as in FIGS. 2 and 3, having a plurality of data tracks recorded on a disk surface in a conventional manner;


FIG. 6 is a block diagram depicting the control functions associated with a disk drive, in accordance with an embodiment of the present invention;


FIG. 7 depicts a plurality of data tracks recorded in a write seldom format in accordance with an exemplary embodiment of the present invention; and


FIGS. 8 through 10 depict a plurality of data tracks recorded in a paired format in accordance with an exemplary embodiment of the present invention.
